		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />On 8kb (64kbit) SRAMs (6264 compatible) pin 26 is positive CE. Since the RAM is 8kb the higher Adress is A12. The shematic you linked is a 16kb (128kbit) EPROM, which does have an A13 at pin 26 instead. You don't want to tie it to VCC unless you want to restrict yourself to 8kb.
<br />
<br />For NROM carts normally no rewiring is needed. It's only needed if you rewire a NROM-128 to a NROM-256 or the other way arround. It looks like you're looking for NROM-128 because of the 16kb (128 kbit) EPROM.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


